@NODE "ABOUT" "What is Mega-Chatter ?"

                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}
Mega-Chatter is a nice little tool I made just for fun. I wanted to have a 
better way to start my chats (when you are a sysop you actually do alot of 
chatting... I do anyway..)  

This door is actually a simple writer, that will write som random txt to the 
user when entering chat. You as sysop have the opportunity to choose which 
type of txt you want to display. You can disply txt in different languages, 
in different moods or whatever. YOU choose.. The txt will be written just as 
if YOU were the one actually writing it. You also have the ability to include
user's handle in the txt... The users will be impressed with you writing 
skills! :-) 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "REQ" "Requirements."

                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}
A Commodore Amiga computer (Pese suxx :-) running on kick 2.0+, /X 
(I guess any version will do...) 

This door uses the AEDoor.libary, so you should have this in LIBS:
(If you haven't got it then call me or your local /X board to get it...) 
@ENDNODE


@NODE "INSTA" "Installation."

                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}
                             
1. Copy the included files to the correct dirs.

2. Edit the nodex/startchat.txt and include:'~CC_CHATTER'

3. If you want, Mega-Chatter can display a txt file before starting the writer,
   if you want this then just call the file chat.txt and put it in 'S:'. 

4. This door does not use a specific pen coulour, so the pen/paper colour can be set
   f.exs in chat.txt

5. Edit and install the @{"Textfiles" LINK "TEXTFILES"}

6. @{"How to operate" LINK "OPERATE"}

Then start chatting!!! 
@ENDNODE

