@NODE "TEXTFILES" "How to use the text files."

                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}
One of the great features of this dooris that you can have up to 10 different 
textfile types. You can for example have one area in your own language, one in 
English end perhaps a area containing jokes, one angry area aso.

To use this feature, first of all you must decide how many areas you want.
Then make one dir for each area (in the same directory as the door was started 
from) Name these dirs with a number, from 1-x (where x is the number of areas 
you want) Now you have to put some files in these areas. You can have as many 
files as you want. Also name these files with a number from 1-x.
There is no need to configure how many areas you have got or how many txt files 
you hvae got in each area, my clever door does it all by it self.

Only the first line of the files will be written. When writing the files you can
use '%U' (case-sensitive) to include user's name) Other functions might be 
included later, so if you have got any ideas of what I might include then tell 
me!

Now it is time to use this great door, but first have a look here ->@{"OPERATION" LINK "OPERATE"} 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "OPERATE" "How to operate Mega-Chatter"

                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}
When started, Mega-Chatter will wait for you to press a key. You have several 
options. Hitting SPACE will display a random file from ALL the areas you have 
got. You can also select which area to pick the file from by hitting a numeric 
key. If you hit f.exs. '1' It will pick a random file in area 1. Hitting '0' 
will pick a file in area 10. If you don't want any txt written, just press any
other button, and it will work just like ordinary chatting....

@ENDNODE
@NODE "NEW" "What is new in this version ?"

*I fixed a bug in connection with the displaying of 'chat.txt'. This file now has 
to be put in 'S:' if you want to use this feature.

Not much bug-fixing, but it was an important fix....

@ENDNODE
